This version is intended to reproduce the original MATLAB code.


- The pole of the mesh is on the y-axis.
  The projected psi is obtained by interpolating the mesh onto a new mesh whose pole is on the z-axis.

- Phi ranges from 0 to pi, and Theta ranges from 0 to pi.

- Note that the following two issues from the original code are not implemented in this version:
  The minimum value of psi is taken as the minimum on x = 1.5, rather than the global minimum.
  Multiple psi fields are merged by adding the normalized projected psi values.

- psi_equilibrium.py still has some issues.